title: CFB: USF Picks Up Homecoming Win Over Winona St.
text:
CFB: USF Picks Up Homecoming Win Over Winona St. October 10, 2015, 10:45 PM SIOUX FALLS, SD - 
The No. 4/5 University of Sioux Falls Football Team totaled more than 600 yards of offense in a 51-30 win over Winona State on Cougar Days. Luke Papilion tied a career-high with five touchdown passes, three of which to Brady Rose, as the Cougars (6-0) erased a 17-3 first-quarter deficit. 
Winona State (3-3) scored their second touchdown on a 77-yard pass from Jack Nelson to take a 17-3 lead in the first half, but USF would score 28 unanswered points before halftime. Jonathon Witt scored on a one-yard TD run before Papilion would have his hand in the next six USF scores. 
Papilion amassed 506 yards of total offense, including 413 yards passing. The junior from Denver, Colo. connected with Brady Rose on consecutive drives to take the lead, 24-17, and he would find Rose again in the second half for the junior h-back's career-high third touchdown grab. Erik Albeck capped off USF's 28-point surge with a 16-yard TD catch just before the half. 
NSIC-leading passer Nelson tossed for 304 yards and connected With Alan May for a air of second-half touchdown passes. USF junior wideout Josh Angulo caught eight balls for 145 yards and tacked on a score in the in the third quarter. 
Earning his first start for the Cougars, running back Justin Fulks toted the ball 31 times and picked up 113 yards on the ground, while Papilion added 93 yards rushing. 
The Cougars head on the road next weekend, facing Southwest Minnesota State in Marshall, Minn. on Oct. 17. 
Eric Zahn
